<DOCNO> APW19990310.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-10 16:21:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  A's, Rookie of Year OK New Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- AL Rookie of the Year Ben Grieve agreed Wednesday  
to a $300,000, one-year contract with the Oakland Athletics. 
</P>
<P>
	A's general manager Billy Beane met Tuesday with Grieve's agent,  
Alan Hendricks. The team hopes to get a multiyear contract 
completed later this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've preserved that opportunity. We still haven't  
accomplished what we set out to do,'' Beane said. ``This just takes 
the focus off the player's contract.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The A's had hoped for a multiyear contract before the start of  
the season. But Todd Helton's $12 million, four-year contract with 
Colorado last week upped Grieve's price, according to Beane. 
</P>
<P>
	``We had a much better chance a week or 10 days ago,'' Beane  
said. ``The Todd Helton contract torpedoed a lot of multiyear deals 
that were being discussed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Grieve, who hit .288 with 18 homers and 89 RBIs last season,  
said he wasn't too concerned with getting a long-term deal before 
the season. 
</P>
<P>
	``I would like to if it is the right deal,'' he said. ``I  
wouldn't want to if it wasn't.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Grieve, the A's first-round draft pick in 1994, was the minor  
league player of the year in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
