<HEADLINE> P&AMP;G Buys Brothers Gourmet Coffees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- The Procter &AMP; Gamble Co. has agreed to buy  
assets of Brothers Gourmet Coffees Inc. of Boca Raton, Fla., for 
$22.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal, announced Tuesday, includes $21.5 million cash and  
$1.3 million in debt. Brothers filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy 
protection in August. 
</P>
<P>
	The purchase, which is expected to close in late April, includes  
portions of Brothers' inventory and other considerations, but not 
the Boca Raton headquarters or a plant in Houston, Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	Brothers had gross sales of about $57 million last year. Its  
gourmet coffees are sold primarily in the Northeast, Southeast and 
Denver areas. 


</P>
</TEXT>
