<HEADLINE> Key Facts About French Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A look at Banque Nationale de Paris and the two French banks it  
is seeking to acquire: 

</P>
<P>
 *Banque Nationale de Paris:    	
</P>
<P>
	-- France's second-largest bank, with total assets of $340  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	-- In addition to domestic and international banking, it also has  
interests in investing, insurance and financial services. 
</P>
<P>
	-- A total of 2,000 bank branches in France.  
</P>
<P>
	-- In the United States, it is the major shareholder in BancWest,  
created by the merger of Bank of the West and First Hawaiian Bank. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Total employees: 52,420, including 12,842 abroad.  

</P>
<P>
 *Societe Generale:    	
</P>
<P>
	-- France's largest private bank with total assets of $412  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Five million individual and corporate customers in France; a  
total of 2,600 branches. 
</P>
<P>
	-- 500 offices abroad in nearly 80 countries.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Total employees: 55,465, including 12,000 outside of France.  

</P>
<P>
 *Paribas:    	
</P>
<P>
	-- A leading investment bank with assets of $246 billion, it also  
is known for its asset management services and serves consumers 
through several subsidiaries. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Total employees: 20,000, including 8,000 outside of France.  


</P>
</TEXT>
