<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Trade Deadline Closing in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The long-rumored Glen Rice deal finally went down Wednesday with  
just one day left before the NBA trading deadline. 
</P>
<P>
	And the rumor mill heated up as other teams weighed whether to  
make major changes so early in the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Rice, a three-time All-Star and one of the league's best  
shooters, was traded from the Charlotte Hornets to the Los Angeles 
Lakers in a five-player deal that sent Elden Campbell and Eddie 
Jones to Charlotte. The Lakers also get B.J. Armstrong and J.R. 
Reid. 
</P>
<P>
	``We feel this takes us one step closer to our ultimate goal of  
having an NBA championship team,'' Lakers vice president Jerry West 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	With other teams also feeling like legitimate championship  
contenders in this first season of the post-Michael Jordan era, 
there was plenty of trade talk going around. 
</P>
<P>
	Some of the discussions centered on Milwaukee point guard  
Terrell Brandon, who will be a free agent at the end of the season 
and has refused to sign an extension with the Bucks. 
</P>
<P>
	``Right now, we're just dealing the cards. The bidding is not in  
yet,'' Bucks coach George Karl said Tuesday night 
</P>
<P>
	By Wednesday night, the bidding was getting interesting.  
</P>
<P>
	One source close to the talks said a number of multiple-team  
trades -- perhaps even a four-team swap -- were being discussed 
involving Brandon, although none of those proposed deals could 
immediately be confirmed. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the names popping up in rumors were Jermaine O'Neal and  
Kelvin Cato of Portland, Derek Anderson of Cleveland, Terry 
Cummings of Golden State, Tyrone Hill of the Bucks and Kendall Gill 
and Chris Gatling of New Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	Several teams were interested in acquiring one of the Los  
Angeles Clippers' players whose contract expires at the end of the 
season, such as Lorenzen Wright, Lamond Murray or Eric Piatkowski. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Neal and Cato have been mentioned in numerous trade rumors for  
the past several weeks, and Gatling has gone so far as to demand a 
trade. The Bucks were one of the teams looking to add a player like 
Gatling to their front line. 
</P>
<P>
	But as always, it was likely there would be much more talk than  
action. 
</P>
<P>
	``The league is conservative and this season is too crazy and  
too short to make major personnel decisions,'' Karl said. ``I think 
you're going to see everybody wait, except for maybe little 
things.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Bucks have been gauging the market for the past few weeks  
trying to decide what to do with Brandon, who has said he'll hold 
to his plans to test the free agent market even if he is traded 
before the end of this season. 
</P>
<P>
	``Unless I get an offer that absolutely knocks my socks off, I'm  
not going to trade him,'' Bucks general manager Bob Weinhauer said. 
</P>
<P>
	The blockbuster Lakers-Hornets deal, rumored for over a month,  
came as the Lakers were on an eight-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a very difficult thing to trade such good players, and  
especially so when they are such quality people,'' West said. ``But 
in Glen Rice, we feel we've acquired the best shooter in the NBA 
and also one of the league's best players. 
</P>
<P>
	The 25 percent turnover of their roster followed by two weeks  
the firing of coach Del Harris and hiring of Kurt Rambis as his 
successor, as well as the signing of forward Dennis Rodman, the 
NBA's leading rebounder for the last seven seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Rice, 31, hasn't played this season following surgery to remove  
loose particles from his right (shooting) elbow in late January. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-8 forward has averaged 20.8 points and 4.8 rebounds  
in nine NBA seasons, six with Miami and the last three with 
Charlotte. He averaged 22.3 points last season to rank sixth in the 
league. 
</P>
<P>
	He figures to step in at small forward for the Lakers, with Kobe  
Bryant moving from that spot to shooting guard, replacing Jones. 
</P>
<P>
	The trade comes three days after the resignation of Hornets  
coach Dave Cowens, who was unhappy with his salary. Charlotte won 
over 50 games each of the last two seasons and made the playoffs, 
but was just 5-11 this year entering Wednesday night's game at 
Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
	``With all of our injuries this season, this trade really gives  
our team two quality starters and a chance to compete for a playoff 
spot,'' general manager Bob Bass said. ``It has greatly improved 
our team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jones' name came up in several trade rumors the last couple of  
years, and he wasn't shy about saying how sick he became because of 
the speculation. 
</P>
<P>
	In fact, after scoring 16 points in a 103-99 victory over the  
Los Angeles Clippers on Tuesday night, he said, ``If it (a trade) 
doesn't happen, it (speculation) will just start up again on July 1 
(the first day of the free-agent signing period). ... It's been 
mentally draining, the whole thing.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
