<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Spike Lee  
</P>
<P>
	 *Image:* Thanks to the raw power of his movies, Spike Lee helped  
spark the urban film boom and has established himself as one of 
Hollywood's most influential filmmakers. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* He was born Shelton Jackson Lee on March 20,  
1957 in Atlanta, the oldest of the five children reared by a jazz 
musician-father and schoolteacher-mother. His mother nicknamed him 
Spike when he was a toddler -- and the name stuck. ``I guess she 
thought I was a tough baby,'' he says. 
</P>
<P>
	The family lived briefly in Chicago before moving to New York in  
1959 and settling in Brooklyn's Fort Greene neighborhood, where Lee 
has established his own production company, 40 Acres and a Mule 
Filmworks. 
</P>
<P>
	He graduated from Morehouse College in Atlanta, then studied at  
New York University's film school for his master's. His student 
film, ``Joe's Bed-Stuy Barbershop: We Cut Heads,'' won a Student 
Academy Award. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Breakout:* ``She's Gotta Have It,'' Lee's first major film, was  
a spirited and sexy romantic comedy. His father Bill Lee wrote the 
musical score. The film won an award at the Cannes Film Festival, 
and set Lee at the forefront of the black wave in American cinema. 
</P>
<P>
	Throughout his career, Lee has focused on dramatizing race  
relations in films like ``School Daze,'' ``Do the Right Thing,'' 
``Jungle Fever'' and ``Malcolm X.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``It's part of the agenda that I stir up controversy,'' he says.  
``When 99 percent of the films that come out of Hollywood are 
mindless entertainment, I guess it will be controversial to do 
something that has substance.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His most recent films include ``He Got Game,'' ``Get on the  
Bus'' and the documentary, ``4 Little Girls.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lee, a longtime New York Knicks fan, has written a book, ``Best  
Seat in the House,'' about his courtside courtship with the game. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:* ``I count my blessings every day because I'm making a  
living doing what makes me happy. Ninety-five percent of the people 
in this world go to their graves never getting to do what makes 
them happy.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays March. 14-20:  
</P>
<P>
	March 14: Actor Michael Caine is 66. Producer Quincy Jones is  
66. Comedian Billy Crystal is 51. Singer-musician Taylor Hanson of 
Hanson is 16. 
</P>
<P>
	March 15: Actor Judd Hirsch is 64. Musician Phil Lesh of The  
Grateful Dead is 59. Singer Mike Love of The Beach Boys is 58. 
Singer-musician Sly Stone of Sly and the Family Stone is 55. 
Musician Howard Scott of War is 53. Singer Dee Snider of Twisted 
Sister is 44. Singer Terence Trent D'Arby is 37. Singer Bret 
Michaels of Poison is 36. Singer Rockwell is 35. 
</P>
<P>
	March 16: Comedian Jerry Lewis is 73. Movie director Bernardo  
Bertolucci is 59. Singer Jerry Jeff Walker is 57. Actor Erik 
Estrada is 50. Actress Kate Nelligan is 48. Musician-singer Nancy 
Wilson of Heart is 45. Actress Isabelle Huppert is 44. Rapper 
Flavor Flav of Public Enemy is 40. 
</P>
<P>
	March 17: Musician Paul Kantner of Jefferson Airplane/Jefferson  
Starship is 58. Singer-songwriter John Sebastian of the Lovin' 
Spoonful is 55. Musician Harold Brown of War is 53. Actor Patrick 
Duffy is 50. Actor Kurt Russell is 48. Actor Gary Sinise is 44. 
Actress Vicki Lewis (``NewsRadio'') is 39. Actor Rob Lowe is 35. 
Singer Billy Corgan of Smashing Pumpkins is 32. Musician Van Connor 
of Screaming Trees is 32. Musician Melissa Auf der Maur of Hole is 
27. 
</P>
<P>
	March 18: Actor Peter Graves is 73. Country singer Charley Pride  
is 61. Singer Wilson Pickett is 58. Singer Irene Cara is 40. Singer 
Vanessa Williams is 36. Musician Jerry Cantrell of Alice in Chains 
is 33. Singer Miki Berenyi of Lush is 32. Rapper-actress Queen 
Latifah is 29. 
</P>
<P>
	March 19: Actress Renee Taylor (``The Nanny'') is 64. Actress  
Ursula Andress is 63. Singer Clarence ``Frogman'' Henry is 62. 
Singer Ruth Pointer of The Pointer Sisters is 53. Actress Glenn 
Close is 52. Actor Bruce Willis is 44. Musician Gert Bettens of K's 
Choice is 29. 
</P>
<P>
	March 20: Producer Carl Reiner is 77. Children's TV host Fred  
Rogers is 71. Actor Hal Linden is 68. Singer Jerry Reed is 62. 
Actor William Hurt is 49. Musician Carl Palmer of Emerson, Lake and 
Palmer is 49. Director Spike Lee is 42. Actress Theresa Russell is 
42. Actress Holly Hunter is 41. Musician Slim Jim Phantom of The 
Stray Cats is 38. 
</P>
