<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Dow Gains 79, Hits New High  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock indexes shot to record highs today as oil  
stocks rose with oil prices, but concerns about earnings at 
technology companies limited the advances in Nasdaq trading. The 
Dow Jones industrial average gained 79.08 to close at 9,772.84, 
surpassing its previous record close of 9,736.08, set last Friday. 
The Nasdaq added 13.07 to finish at 2,406.01, still shy of its 
all-time closing high of 2,510.09 on Feb 1. The Dow is now up 6.4 
percent for the year. Oil stocks were sharply higher following 
reports that a Saudi official said the world's oil producers are 
close to an agreement to cut production to shore up prices. Stocks 
got another boost as Ralph Acampora, director of technical research 
at Prudential Securities and a well-known market bull, told a group 
of Belgian traders that U.S. equities, especially blue-chip Dow 
components, are in the ``early stages of another bull market.'' 

</P>
