apples and two kinds of cherries, all varieties that the United 
States had pressured Tokyo to approve. The decision comes two weeks 
after a World Trade Organization appeals panel ruled that Japan 
acted illegally by blocking imports of fruit such as apples and 
cherries on health grounds. The apples to be permitted are 
Braeburn, Fuji, Gala, Granny Smith and Jona Gold. The cherries are 
Lapin and Sweet Heart. 

