<HEADLINE> Seminoles Extend Coaches' Contracts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Steve Robinson's .500 record as  
basketball coach at Florida State the last two seasons netted him a 
two-year contract extension Wednesday, athletic director Dave Hart 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Hart also extended the contract of women's basketball coach Sue  
Semrau, who was 16-38 in her first two seasons. Both coaches are 
now under 5-year agreements. 
</P>
<P>
	``This decision represents an acknowledgment of the substantial  
rebuilding jobs both coaches have undertaken and an appreciation 
for the manner in which they have gone about their respective 
tasks,'' Hart said. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson was paid $415,891 last year, and Semrau $120,800.  
</P>
<P>
	Robinson went 18-14 in his first season at Florida State and  
reached the NCAA tournament with a team made up largely of players 
recruited by previous coach Pat Kennedy, who is now at DePaul. 
</P>
<P>
	The Seminoles slipped to 13-17 this year, winning just two games  
in the final six weeks of the season. They are 12-23 in Atlantic 
Coach Conference play under Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
	The women's team is 7-27 in ACC play since Semrau replaced Chris  
Gobrecht, who broke her 5-year contract with the school and left 
after just one season to become coach at her alma mater, Southern 
California. Florida State sued Gobrecht and the parties reached an 
out-of-court settlement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
