<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Meissnitzer Takes Downhill in Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SIERRA NEVADA, Spain (AP) -- Alexandra Meissnitzer, who wrapped  
up the overall World Cup title last week, won the downhill today in 
the World Cup final. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Meissnitzer's eighth World Cup victory of the season --  
second in downhill. She also has four giant slalom victories and 
two in super-G. 
</P>
<P>
	The 25-year-old Austrian finished in 1 minute, 54.16 seconds by  
about .3 seconds. Norway's Ingeborg Helen Marken was second in 
1:54.47, followed by Canadian Melanie Turgeon in 1:54.70 and Renate 
Goetschl of Austria, who was fourth in 1:54.97. 
</P>
<P>
	The race had little importance for Goetschl, who clinched the  
World Cup season downhill title last week in St. Moritz and won 
four of the nine downhills this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
