<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Denmark Bank. Insurance Co. Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) -- Denmark's second-largest banking  
group, Unibank, is merging with Tryg-Baltica, the country's largest 
non-life insurance company. 
</P>
<P>
	Under the merger plan, which must be approved by shareholders,  
the companies will be sister subsidiaries under the Unidanmark 
group, Unibank's parent company. The two will retain their own 
brand names and logos. 
</P>
<P>
	Unibank, which was formed in 1990 from the merger of three  
Danish banks, is the principal subsidiary of Unidanmark. The 
insurance group was created five years later when the companies 
Tryg and Baltica merged. 
</P>
<P>
	Unibank and Tryg-Baltica had a total pretax profit last year of  
$780 million and about 13,200 employees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
