<HEADLINE>  Dollar Falls, Tokyo Stock Prices Up / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar fell against the yen on today as Japan's  
key stock index soared to a seven month high. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar fell to 120.54 yen in late afternoon trading, down  
1.22 yen from late Tuesday in Tokyo, and less than its late New 
York level of 121.00 yen overnight. 
</P>
