<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Light snow lingered over some parts of the East on Wednesday  
while high pressure pushing in from Canada brought colder, drier 
air to the Midwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Parts of West Virginia, Pennsylvania and Maryland saw some snow  
showers but no significant accumulations. 
</P>
<P>
	Colder, drier air moved into the Great Lakes, Ohio Valley and  
Northeast early Wednesday with fair to clear skies in most areas. 
</P>
<P>
	The Southeast and Tennessee Valley also saw fair skies while  
clouds and a few light sprinkles were reported across the 
lower-Mississippi Valley and southern Plains into Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	Light snow fell in the northern and central Plains states while  
most of the western United States experienced fair, dry weather. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a morning low of  
minus 17 degrees in Saranac Lake, N.Y., to an afternoon high of 84 
degrees in the Texas cities of McAllen and Harlingen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
