<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stock Prices Rise / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stock prices rose Thursday, boosted by a  
surge earlier on Wall Street. The dollar slipped against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nikkei Stock Average rose 81.43 points, or 0.53 percent, to  
close the morning session at 15,561.43. On Wednesday, the index 
jumped 383.30 points, or 2.54 percent, jumping to its highest level 
since Aug. 10. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 119.42 yen at midday, down 1.12 yen from late  
Wednesday in Tokyo and also below its level of 119.88 yen in New 
York. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, share prices rose on Wall Street's jump to  
a new record and improved market sentiment in Tokyo, analysts said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones industrial average rose 79.08 points Wednesday, or  
0.8 percent, to 9,772.84, surpassing its previous record close set 
last Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nikkei has gained more than 700 points in the last two  
trading days on hopes for aggressive restructuring steps at 
Japanese companies. 
</P>
<P>
	Optimism was fueled by electronics giant Sony Corp.'s  
announcement of plans to take over three publicly listed 
subsidiaries and eliminate 10 percent of its work force. This 
pushed up the company's shares nearly 40 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Sony issues plunged on Thursday, however, as investors took  
profits prompted by the dollar's moderate weakening against the 
yen, traders said. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section rose 9.25 points, or 0.78 percent, to 1,196.72. The 
TOPIX rose 24.96 points, or 2.15 percent the previous day. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency trading, the dollar fell on profit taking by  
Japanese exporters and U.S. funds, traders said. 
</P>
<P>
	Also on Thursday, the head of the International Bureau at  
Japan's Ministry of Finance expressed hope for stability in foreign 
exchange markets. 
</P>
<P>
	Speaking to reporters upon arriving at the ministry, Haruhiko  
Kuroda said, ``Stable foreign exchange is desirable.'' He wouldn't 
comment on specific exchange rates. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 131.03 yen, below  
131.10 yen in New York late Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the 10-year Japanese government bond rose to 1.755  
percent from Wednesday's finish of 1.670 percent, driving its price 
down to 100.35 yen from 101.04 yen. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
