<HEADLINE> 13-Year-Old Guilty of Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW PHILADELPHIA, Ohio (AP) -- A 13-year-old boy who helped  
search for a missing 5-year-old playmate after the girl's mother 
paid him $5 has been convicted of stabbing the child to death. 
</P>
<P>
	Anthony Harris was found guilty Wednesday of juvenile charges of  
murder in last summer's slaying of Devan Duniver. Anthony could be 
held until he is 21. No sentencing date was set. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know what malevolence has filled your soul when this  
took place,'' Judge Linda Kate said to an expressionless Harris. 
``I sincerely hope that some time you will find some type of 
salvation because if you do not, your life will be an endless 
night.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Kate's words brought a sob from Devan's mother, Lori Duniver,  
who later lashed out at the boy. 
</P>
<P>
	``He showed absolutely, positively no remorse,'' she said. ``He  
needs the death sentence. He deserves what my daughter got.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Defense attorney Tarin Hale said he will ask for probation and  
will appeal the conviction. 
</P>
<P>
	Devan's body was found June 28 underneath brush in the woods  
near the complex of townhouses where she and Anthony lived in this 
city about 70 miles south of Cleveland. Prosecutors said Anthony 
confessed. 
</P>
<P>
	Devan's mother said the boy joined the search for her daughter  
after she gave him $5. He wanted the money so he could go to a 
tractor pull. 
</P>
<P>
	The prosecution's case relied mostly on Harris' confession and  
testimony from Devan's friends and family members, who said the 
girl was frightened of Harris because he threatened her shortly 
before she was killed. 
</P>
<P>
	Defense attorneys suggested Devan was stabbed elsewhere and that  
the killer then moved her body to the spot where it was found. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
