keep him from leading a pack of five mushers dashing from Nikolai 
to Takotna early today in the Iditarod Trail Sled Dog Race. 
Swingley drove his team into the Takotna checkpoint at 2:14 a.m. 
Five-time Iditarod winner Rick Swenson was second at 3:56 a.m., 
followed within an hour by defending champion Jeff King of Denali 
Park, DeeDee Jonrowe of Willow and John Barron of Big Lake. 

