</P>
<P>
	The Fraternal Order of Eagles in Eastpointe lent the use of its  
hall for the fund-raiser and dozens of businesses donated gifts for 
auction. About 50 people paid $5 admission. 
</P>
<P>
	``Everybody just sort of fell for it,'' said Barbara Martin, 60,  
the club's secretary. 
</P>
