<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Flyers Get Recchi From Montreal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia Flyers obtained right wing  
Mark Recchi from the Montreal Canadiens on Wednesday for 
right-winger Dainius Zubrus and a pair of draft picks. 
</P>
<P>
	The Canadiens will get the Flyers' second-round pick in 1999 or  
2000 as well as either a seventh-round pick in 1999 or a 
sixth-rounder in 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	Recchi, 31, was the Canadiens' scoring leader with 47 points,  
but has only 12 goals this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Flyers general manager Bob Clarke said he expects Recchi to play  
for the Flyers against the Colorado Avalanche on Thursday, one day 
after he played for the Montreal Canadiens against the St. Louis 
Blues. 
</P>
<P>
	The Flyers are on an eight-game winless streak, having lost five  
in a row before getting ties in their last three games. 
</P>
<P>
	Zubrus, 20, has three goals and five assists in 63 games this  
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Recchi, 31, is returning to Philadelphia. He played portions of  
four seasons for the Flyers, leading the team in scoring in each of 
his two full seasons with the team. In 1991-92 and 1994-95, Recchi 
got 105 goals and 157 assists for 262 points and 171 penalty 
minutes in 200 games. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Montreal's second trade in as many days. The Canadiens  
acquired defenseman Scott Lachance from the New York Islanders on 
Tuesday for a third-round draft pick. 
</P>
<P>
	Clarke said the Recchi deal took awhile to negotiate.  
</P>
<P>
	``They thought they should get Danius and the first-round  
pick,'' Clark said, but he wasn't willing to give up next season's 
first-round pick. 
</P>
</TEXT>
