<DOCNO> APW19990310.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-10 14:46:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sore Achilles Will Sideline Ewing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PURCHASE, N.Y. (AP) -- Patrick Ewing will remain sidelined  
indefinitely with a sore Achilles' tendon, and just like last 
season -- although not for as long -- the New York Knicks will have 
to learn to live without him. 
</P>
<P>
	``All I know is that it's hurting, and hopefully when the  
swelling goes away the pain will go away and I can get back to the 
team,'' Ewing said Wednesday after practice as the Knicks prepared 
to begin a stretch of five games in six days. 
</P>
<P>
	Whether Ewing plays in any of those games remains to be seen.  
The team officially listed him as day-to-day, although it seems 
certain they will take a conservative approach to bringing Ewing 
back. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm going to wait until it starts feeling better to decide  
that,'' Ewing said when asked whether he'll wait until he feels 100 
percent recovered. ``I want to be out there, but I definitely don't 
want to miss the season again.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, a broken wrist sidelined Ewing for the final 56  
games of the regular season and the first round of the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	Ewing suffered that injury against Milwaukee, and there was an  
eerie similarity Tuesday night as the Knicks were playing the same 
team as Ewing walked off the court just 29 seconds into the first 
quarter grimacing in pain. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought I tore it,'' Ewing said.  
</P>
<P>
	An MRI revealed no serious injury to the tendon, but Ewing said  
it remained sore Wednesday. He wasn't predicting a quick return. 
</P>
<P>
	In his absence, the Knicks are likely to start Chris Dudley at  
center, although coach Jeff Van Gundy said Latrell Sprewell might 
move into the starting lineup with Larry Johnson moving to power 
forward and Kurt Thomas to center. 
</P>
<P>
	Yet another option would be to start Marcus Camby at center.  
</P>
<P>
	Unlike last year, when Buck Williams and Terry Cummings were on  
the team and the Knicks went 28-28 after Ewing went down, the 
Knicks do not have a lot of offensive depth on the front line. 
</P>
<P>
	They also are among the worst rebounding teams in the league,  
and Ewing was leading them in that category. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've been working hard just in case a situation like this does  
come up,'' said Dudley, who broke an 11-game scoreless drought in 
Tuesday's loss to the Bucks. ``You hope it doesn't happen, but it 
has happened.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Tuesday's loss was the Knicks' third by one point in the past  
four games, and Van Gundy clearly has become frustrated with his 
team's lack of mental toughness on the road and the absence of 
sound decision-making down the stretch of close games. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am tired of us playing our worst when our best is needed.  
That's the bottom line,'' he said. ``I'm not fearful of anything 
except not winning. It has nothing to do with Patrick's absence. We 
did this drill last year. 
</P>
<P>
	``We weren't fearful last year; we're not going to be fearful  
this year. We've played five close games and lost four of the five, 
and we've lost three one-point games in the last week. That's the 
difference between being eighth and ninth for the playoffs or in 
first place.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
