<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 13-Year-Old Guilty of Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW PHILADELPHIA, Ohio (AP) -- A 13-year-old boy who helped  
search for a missing 5-year-old playmate after the little girl's 
mother paid him $5 was convicted Wednesday of stabbing the child to 
death. 
</P>
<P>
	A judge found Anthony Harris guilty of juvenile charges of  
murder in the slaying last summer of Devan Duniver. 
</P>
<P>
	Anthony could be held until he is 21. No sentencing date was  
set. 
</P>
<P>
	Devan's body was found June 28 underneath brush in the woods  
near the complex of townhouses where she and Anthony lived in this 
city about 70 miles south of Cleveland. Prosecutors said Anthony 
confessed. 
</P>
<P>
	Devan's mother, Lori Duniver, said the boy joined the search for  
her daughter after she gave him $5. He wanted the money so he could 
go to a tractor pull. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
