<HEADLINE> Susan Lucci in Alaska for Iditarod </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANCHORAGE, Alaska (AP) -- She's not going to win this contest,  
either, but that doesn't bother Susan Lucci. 
</P>
<P>
	Lucci, who plays Erica Kane on ABC's ``All My Children'' and has  
failed in 18 tries to win a Daytime Emmy, spent last weekend in the 
world of sled dogs and mushers, watching the start of the Iditarod 
Trail Sled Dog Race. 
</P>
<P>
	At Saturday's ceremonial start, Lucci was an ``Iditarider,''  
zipping through downtown Anchorage while sitting in Rick Mackey's 
sled. Mackey won the 1,100-mile race in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've always read about the Iditarod in The New York Times, and  
I've always been curious about Alaska,'' said Lucci, who added that 
she was awed by the state's rugged terrain. 
</P>
<P>
	Other celebrity Iditariders included Joan Rivers, Gary Collins  
and wife Mary Ann Mobley. 
</P>
