<HEADLINE> Bullet Hits School Bus in Calif. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- A bullet struck a school bus carrying  
special education students and injured a man who was walking 
nearby, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The bullet hit the back of the bus and sailed through a window  
on the opposite side, police spokesman Doug Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
	The injured pedestrian was hit in the torso while walking toward  
his car, Anderson said. Three students in their teens were on the 
bus. None were injured. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's still unknown if it was one shot, two shots, or if the  
bus was the intended target,'' Anderson said. ``Some witnesses 
heard one gunshot, others heard two.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The bullet passed through a section of the bus where none of the  
students were seated. 
</P>
<P>
	The injured man, who has not been identified, was hospitalized  
in stable condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
