<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-10 06:55:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wall St. Stocks Open Higher / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened higher with the Dow  
Jones Industrial Average up five points in this morning's early 
going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 7-to-5 lead 
over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 14 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up nearly two points. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks appear to have a little bit of wiggle room here, but  
market-watchers don't expect to see much of a move higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The concern is a familiar one -- corporate earnings.  
</P>
<P>
	Yesterday's about-face, which led to small losses on the  
session, came after rumors swirled about weakness in the high-tech 
sector. 
</P>
<P>
	Some of the Asian markets were solidly higher overnight. But  
European markets are narrowly mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	Bond prices are fairly steady.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
